---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RegimeDiagram from '../components/RegimeDiagram.astro';
import { TEST_COUNT, IDENTITY_COUNT, DOMAIN_COUNT, TEST_FILE_COUNT } from '../lib/metrics';
---

<BaseLayout title="Regime Classification — GCD" description="The three-regime classification system: Stable, Watch, Collapse. Four frozen gates, Fisher space geometry, regime transitions, cross-domain evidence, and the interactive phase diagram — all derived from Axiom-0.">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-12">

    <!-- ═══ HEADER ═══ -->
    <header class="border-b border-kernel-800 pb-8">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-kernel-600 tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">Regime Classification</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-3">
        The Three Regimes of Collapse
      </h1>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-lg max-w-3xl">
        Every system in GCD occupies exactly one of three regimes — <strong class="text-emerald-400">Stable</strong>,
        <strong class="text-amber-400">Watch</strong>, or <strong class="text-red-400">Collapse</strong> —
        determined by four frozen gates applied to the kernel invariants. The regime is <em>derived</em>, never asserted.
        Stability is rare: 87.5% of the Fisher manifold lies outside it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-kernel-500 text-sm mt-2 italic">
        Ruptura est fons constantiae — dissolution is the source of constancy.
      </p>
      <nav class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-5" aria-label="Page sections">
        <a href="#overview" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Overview</a>
        <a href="#gates" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Four Gates</a>
        <a href="#regimes" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Regime Profiles</a>
        <a href="#critical" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Critical Overlay</a>
        <a href="#geometry" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Geometry</a>
        <a href="#transitions" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Transitions</a>
        <a href="#gap" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Heterogeneity Gap</a>
        <a href="#cross-domain" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Cross-Domain</a>
        <a href="#explorer" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Live Explorer</a>
        <a href="#phase-diagram" class="text-xs bg-kernel-800 hover:bg-kernel-700 text-kernel-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded transition">Phase Diagram</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         §1  OVERVIEW — WHY THREE REGIMES?
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="overview">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;1 &mdash; Why Three Regimes?</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        The regime system translates continuous kernel invariants into discrete structural phases. Verdicts are derived from gates, never asserted.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-4">The Partition of Fisher Space</h3>
        <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-4">
          The kernel K&nbsp;:&nbsp;[0,1]<sup>n</sup>&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;&Delta;<sup>n</sup>&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;(F,&nbsp;&omega;,&nbsp;S,&nbsp;C,&nbsp;&kappa;,&nbsp;IC) produces continuous invariants.
          Four frozen gates discretize this into three regimes, partitioning the entire 4-dimensional Fisher manifold.
          The gates are <em>conjunctive</em> for Stable &mdash; all four must be satisfied simultaneously &mdash;
          which is why stability is structurally rare.
        </p>

        <!-- Fisher space partition bar -->
        <div class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex h-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-inner border border-kernel-700">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-emerald-100" style="width: 12.5%; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #059669, #10b981)">12.5%</div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-amber-100" style="width: 24.4%; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b)">24.4%</div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-red-100" style="width: 63.1%; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #ef4444)">63.1%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between text-[10px] text-kernel-500 mt-1.5 font-mono px-1">
            <span>Stable</span>
            <span>Watch</span>
            <span>Collapse</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-emerald-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-emerald-500"></span>
              <h4 class="text-emerald-400 font-bold">Stable</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">Low drift, high fidelity, low entropy, low curvature. All four gates satisfied. The quiet zone &mdash; only 12.5% of the manifold qualifies.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-amber-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-amber-500"></span>
              <h4 class="text-amber-400 font-bold">Watch</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">Moderate drift or a Stable gate not met. The intermediate zone where most &ldquo;interesting&rdquo; dynamics live &mdash; curvature cost often dominates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-red-800/40 rounded-lg p-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-red-500"></span>
              <h4 class="text-red-400 font-bold">Collapse</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">High drift (&omega;&nbsp;&ge;&nbsp;0.30). The dominant regime &mdash; 63.1% of the manifold. Not failure but the generative boundary that makes return meaningful.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-kernel-500">
        <strong class="text-kernel-300">Key structural insight:</strong> Collapse is not an error state.
        <em>Ruptura est fons constantiae</em> &mdash; dissolution is the source of constancy.
        The axiom (&ldquo;only what returns is real&rdquo;) requires a boundary to return <em>from</em>.
        Collapse provides that boundary. 63.1% of the manifold is generative territory.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         §2  THE FOUR GATES
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="gates">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;2 &mdash; The Four Gates</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        Four frozen thresholds &mdash; seam-derived, not prescribed &mdash; classify every kernel output into a regime.
        Stable is <em>conjunctive</em>: all four gates must be satisfied simultaneously.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="text-left border-b border-kernel-700">
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-kernel-400 font-semibold">Gate</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-kernel-400 font-semibold">Symbol</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-kernel-400 font-semibold">Stable Threshold</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-kernel-400 font-semibold">What It Measures</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-kernel-300">
            <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-bold text-amber-400">Drift Gate</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">&omega;</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">&lt; 0.038</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-kernel-400 text-xs">How much signal is lost to collapse (1 &minus; F). Primary regime variable.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-bold text-blue-400">Fidelity Gate</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">F</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">&gt; 0.90</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-kernel-400 text-xs">What fraction of coherence survives collapse. Arithmetic mean of channels.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-kernel-800">
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-bold text-purple-400">Entropy Gate</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">S</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">&lt; 0.15</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-kernel-400 text-xs">Bernoulli field entropy &mdash; uncertainty of the collapse field.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-bold text-cyan-400">Curvature Gate</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">C</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono">&lt; 0.14</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-kernel-400 text-xs">Channel heterogeneity &mdash; coupling to uncontrolled degrees of freedom.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Gate logic diagram -->
      <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-4">Classification Logic</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 font-mono text-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-bold w-24 shrink-0">COLLAPSE</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-400">&omega;&nbsp;&ge;&nbsp;0.30</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-600 text-xs ml-auto">(primary boundary)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-kernel-800"></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-emerald-400 font-bold w-24 shrink-0">STABLE</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-400">&omega;&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;0.038 &nbsp;<strong class="text-kernel-300">AND</strong>&nbsp; F&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;0.90 &nbsp;<strong class="text-kernel-300">AND</strong>&nbsp; S&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;0.15 &nbsp;<strong class="text-kernel-300">AND</strong>&nbsp; C&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;0.14</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-600 text-xs ml-auto">(conjunctive)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-kernel-800"></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold w-24 shrink-0">WATCH</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-400">everything else</span>
            <span class="text-kernel-600 text-xs ml-auto">(default)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs mt-4 italic">
          Stable is conjunctive because stability requires <em>all</em> invariants to be simultaneously clean.
          A single gate violation drops the system to Watch, even if the other three are perfect.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Why these thresholds? -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Why &omega; = 0.038?</h4>
          <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">3.8% drift is the empirical boundary where all four Stable gates can plausibly be met. Below this threshold F&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;0.962, and S and C are typically sufficiently low. Above it, the chances of satisfying all four gates simultaneously drops sharply.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Why &omega; = 0.30?</h4>
          <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">At 30% drift, the system has lost nearly a third of its coherence. The drift cost closure &Gamma;(&omega;) begins its steep cubic ascent. This is where return from collapse requires structural intervention, not incremental correction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Why F &gt; 0.90?</h4>
          <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">90% fidelity is the floor for stability. Below it, even with low drift (which is constrained by F + &omega; = 1), the system cannot maintain coherence across channels reliably.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Why S &lt; 0.15 and C &lt; 0.14?</h4>
          <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">These thresholds ensure that the collapse field is locally ordered (low entropy) and channels are approximately homogeneous (low curvature). The maximum Bernoulli field entropy is ln&nbsp;2&nbsp;&asymp;&nbsp;0.693, so 0.15 is about 22% of maximum &mdash; very constrained.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         §3  REGIME PROFILES — DEEP CHARACTERIZATION
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="regimes">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;3 &mdash; Regime Profiles</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        Each regime has a distinct signature across all six kernel invariants and a characteristic return dynamic.
      </p>

      <div id="regime-profiles" class="space-y-4">
        <!-- Stable profile -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border-l-4 border-emerald-500 rounded-r-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <span class="w-4 h-4 rounded bg-emerald-500"></span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-400">Stable</h3>
            <span class="text-kernel-500 text-xs font-mono ml-auto">12.5% of Fisher space</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-6 gap-2 mb-4" id="stable-invariants">
            <!-- Filled by script -->
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Kernel Signature</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>F &gt; 0.90 &mdash; very high coherence survival</li>
                <li>&omega; &lt; 0.038 &mdash; negligible drift</li>
                <li>S &lt;0.15 &mdash; low entropy, collapse field is ordered</li>
                <li>C &lt; 0.14 &mdash; channels are nearly homogeneous</li>
                <li>IC/F &gt; 0.95 &mdash; minimal heterogeneity gap</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Return Dynamics</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>&Gamma;(&omega;) &lt; 10<sup>&minus;5</sup> &mdash; drift cost negligible</li>
                <li>&tau;_R* dominated by memory term &Delta;&kappa;</li>
                <li>Budget runs surplus &mdash; system generates credit</li>
                <li>Basin requires O(&epsilon;&sup2;) perturbation to escape</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs mt-3 italic">Typical: healthy atoms, well-calibrated instruments, equilibrium systems.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Watch profile -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <span class="w-4 h-4 rounded bg-amber-500"></span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Watch</h3>
            <span class="text-kernel-500 text-xs font-mono ml-auto">24.4% of Fisher space</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-6 gap-2 mb-4" id="watch-invariants">
            <!-- Filled by script -->
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Kernel Signature</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>F &asymp; 0.70&ndash;0.90 &mdash; moderate coherence</li>
                <li>&omega; &asymp; 0.038&ndash;0.30 &mdash; measurable drift</li>
                <li>S &asymp; 0.15&ndash;0.40 &mdash; moderate entropy</li>
                <li>C &asymp; 0.14&ndash;0.50 &mdash; visible channel spread</li>
                <li>IC/F &asymp; 0.70&ndash;0.95 &mdash; moderate heterogeneity gap</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Return Dynamics</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>&Gamma;(&omega;) &asymp; 0.1&ndash;1.0 &mdash; drift cost measurable</li>
                <li>&tau;_R* dominated by curvature cost &alpha;&middot;C</li>
                <li>Budget near break-even &mdash; costly but feasible return</li>
                <li>&Gamma; and &alpha;C compete for dominance</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs mt-3 italic">Typical: composites, biological systems, financial portfolios, mid-scale physics.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Collapse profile -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <span class="w-4 h-4 rounded bg-red-500"></span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">Collapse</h3>
            <span class="text-kernel-500 text-xs font-mono ml-auto">63.1% of Fisher space</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-6 gap-2 mb-4" id="collapse-invariants">
            <!-- Filled by script -->
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Kernel Signature</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>F &lt; 0.70 &mdash; majority of coherence lost</li>
                <li>&omega; &ge; 0.30 &mdash; high or extreme drift</li>
                <li>S &gt; 0.40 &mdash; high uncertainty in collapse field</li>
                <li>C &gt; 0.50 &mdash; severe channel heterogeneity</li>
                <li>IC/F &lt; 0.70 &mdash; large heterogeneity gap, dead channels</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Return Dynamics</h4>
              <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>&Gamma;(&omega;) &gt; 100 &mdash; drift cost overwhelms curvature</li>
                <li>&tau;_R* dominated by drift cost &Gamma;(&omega;)</li>
                <li>Budget in deep deficit &mdash; structural intervention needed</li>
                <li>Beyond &omega;_trap &asymp; 0.682: trapping &mdash; no single-step escape</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs mt-3 italic">Typical: confinement (quarks &rarr; hadrons), phase boundaries, system failure, deep restructuring.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         §4  CRITICAL OVERLAY
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="critical">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;4 &mdash; Critical Overlay</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        Critical is <em>not</em> a regime &mdash; it is a severity flag that can accompany any regime. It signals that composite integrity has collapsed.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-violet-700/50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="w-4 h-4 rounded bg-violet-600"></span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-violet-400">CRITICAL: IC &lt; 0.30</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-600 rounded p-4 text-center mb-4">
          <span class="font-mono text-xl text-violet-400">IC = exp(&kappa;) &lt; 0.30</span>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">What IC &lt; 0.30 means</h4>
            <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Integrity is dangerously low &mdash; the weighted geometric mean has collapsed</li>
              <li>One or more channels are near-dead (c<sub>i</sub> &rarr; &epsilon;)</li>
              <li>Geometric slaughter: even if F is healthy, IC crashes</li>
              <li>The seam budget becomes very expensive</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Overlay behavior</h4>
            <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Can appear in <em>any</em> regime &mdash; even Watch with moderate &omega;</li>
              <li>In the phase diagram, Critical is rendered as a violet tint</li>
              <li>Takes precedence in the classification cascade</li>
              <li>Signals structural fragility regardless of drift level</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-kernel-500">
        <strong class="text-kernel-300">Example:</strong> A system with &omega; = 0.20 (Watch) but one dead channel can have IC = 0.08 &mdash;
        the system appears moderate by drift alone, but is structurally fragile. The Critical overlay catches what the drift gate misses.
        This is the power of <em>multiplicative</em> coherence: one dead channel kills the geometric mean.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         §5  GEOMETRY — FISHER SPACE AND THE BERNOULLI MANIFOLD
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="geometry">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;5 &mdash; Geometry of the Regime Manifold</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        The kernel lives on the Bernoulli manifold &mdash; the space of binary channel probabilities c &isin; [0,1]<sup>n</sup>.
        Regime boundaries are geometric structures in Fisher coordinates.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-3">Fisher Coordinates</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-600 rounded p-3 text-center mb-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-amber-400">&theta; = arccos(&radic;F)</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="text-kernel-400 text-xs space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>The Bernoulli manifold is <strong class="text-kernel-200">flat</strong> in Fisher coordinates: g<sub>F</sub>(&theta;) = 1</li>
            <li>All structure comes from the <em>embedding</em>, not intrinsic curvature</li>
            <li>F + &omega; = 1 becomes sin&sup2;&theta; + cos&sup2;&theta; = 1 &mdash; an exact trigonometric identity</li>
            <li>Regime boundaries are arcs at fixed &theta; values</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-5">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-3">The Equator</h3>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-600 rounded p-3 text-center mb-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-cyan-400">c = &frac12;, &theta; = &pi;/4</span>
