         §7  HETEROGENEITY GAP
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section id="gap">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">&sect;7 &mdash; Heterogeneity Gap per Regime</h2>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-sm mb-5">
        The heterogeneity gap &Delta; = F &minus; IC measures how much channel heterogeneity costs integrity.
        It is the central diagnostic across regimes.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-600 rounded p-4 text-center mb-4">
          <span class="font-mono text-xl text-amber-400">&Delta; = F &minus; IC</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-kernel-500 mt-1">Arithmetic mean minus geometric mean of channels</span>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-emerald-800/30 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-2">Stable: &Delta; &asymp; 0&ndash;0.05</h4>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">All channels strong, approximately homogeneous. IC &asymp; F. Negligible gap &mdash; the geometric and arithmetic means nearly coincide.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-amber-800/30 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-amber-400 mb-2">Watch: &Delta; &asymp; 0.05&ndash;0.30</h4>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">Some channels weaken, creating spread. IC drops faster than F. The gap reveals which channels need attention &mdash; the &ldquo;interesting zone&rdquo; for diagnostics.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-red-800/30 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-red-400 mb-2">Collapse: &Delta; &asymp; 0.30&ndash;0.90</h4>
            <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">Severe heterogeneity. Dead channels (c<sub>i</sub> &rarr; &epsilon;) kill IC while F remains positive. This is geometric slaughter &mdash; one dead channel destroys multiplicative coherence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- The two-channel formula -->
        <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-600 rounded p-4">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Two-Channel Formula</h4>
          <div class="text-center mb-2">
            <span class="font-mono text-sm text-cyan-400">
              &Delta; = (c<sub>1</sub> + c<sub>2</sub>)/2 &minus; &radic;(c<sub>1</sub> &middot; c<sub>2</sub>)
              = (&radic;c<sub>1</sub> &minus; &radic;c<sub>2</sub>)&sup2; / 2
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-kernel-400 text-xs">
            The gap is always non-negative (the integrity bound IC &le; F). For n channels it satisfies the asymptotic bound
            &Delta; &asymp; Var(c) / (2F) &mdash; the Fisher Information contribution from heterogeneity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Geometric slaughter example -->
      <div class="bg-kernel-950 border border-kernel-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">Geometric Slaughter (Lemma 47)</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-center mb-3" id="slaughter-values">
          <!-- Filled by script -->
        </div>
        <p class="text-kernel-500 text-xs">
          8-channel trace: 7 channels perfect (c = 1), 1 channel dead (c = &epsilon;).
          F stays healthy &mdash; the arithmetic mean barely notices one dead channel.
          But IC crashes to &epsilon;<sup>1/8</sup> &asymp; 0.10 &mdash; the geometric mean is destroyed by a single weak link.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

